      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Propose a structure for compound <b>C</b>, which has M<sup>+</sup> = 86 in its mass spectrum, an IR absorption at 3400 cm<sup>–1</sup>, and the following <sup>13</sup>C NMR spectral data:</p>\n<p><b>Compound C</b></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:none\">\n<li>Broadband-decoupled <sup>13</sup>C NMR: 30.2, 31.9, 61.8, 114.7, 138.4 <i>δ</i></li>\n<li>DEPT-90: 138.4 <i>δ</i></li>\n<li>DEPT-135: positive peak at 138.4 <i>δ</i>; negative peaks at 30.2, 31.9, 61.8, 114.7 <i>δ</i></li>\n</ul>",
